ing this reconnaissance.\n\n- **Technologies**:\n  - Web server: `Apache/2.4.65 (Debian)` (from multiple responses).\n  - Frontend: Bootstrap CSS via `/static/css/bootstrap.min.css`.\n\n- **Suspicious / Interesting Behavior Relevant to ID Fuzzing**:\n  - Hidden `user_id` field with value `10032` on `/password/test` is a clear numeric identifier likely associated with the user `test` (shown as "Welcome, John!"). This discrepancy between displayed name (John) and username/test suggests an internal user mapping and makes `user_id` a primary candidate for later fuzzing with nearby values (e.g., 10031, 10033, etc.).\n  - Username appears in both:\n    - Request body (`username=test`), and\n    - URL path (`/password/test`), and\n    - Hidden field (`username` value="test"). This redundancy provides multiple locations where ID-like values (usernames) could later be manipulated/fuzzed.\n  - The root page explicitly references a test account in an HTML comment, which may indicate the app is in a testing/demo state and might have weak or predictable ID schemes.\n\n## Filter/WAF Analysis\n- **Blocked**: None observed. No evidence of WAF or input filtering behavior yet; only simple username submission has been tested.\n- **Allowed**: Basic alphanumeric username `test` was accepted and led to a valid redirect.\n- **Bypass Method**: None used or needed at this reconnaissance stage.\n\n## Failed Approaches (Do Not Retry)\n- None yet; reconnaissance has only performed straightforward GET/POST requests with valid parameters and has not attempted invalid/fuzzed IDs or malicious payloads.\n\n## Credentials & Tokens\n- **Potential test credentials** (from HTML comment on `/`):\n  - Type: Test account hint\n  - Value: `test:test`\n  - Source: `<!-- TODO: Delete the testing account (test:test). -->`\n- No cookies, session tokens, JWTs, or API keys discovered.\n\n## Next Steps\n- [ ] Use the hinted test account (`test` as username and likely `test` as password) to complete the login flow