SUBTASK: Create and execute a Python script to systematically fuzz the user_id parameter with values 10030-10040 via batch POST requests to /password/test endpoint

TARGET: /password/test endpoint with POST method

PAYLOAD/TECHNIQUE: Iterate through user_id values 10030, 10031, 10032, 10033, 10034, 10035, 10036, 10037, 10038, 10039, 10040. For each value, send authenticated POST request with payload: username=test&user_id={value}&password=test. Maintain session using Flask session cookie.

EXPECTED OUTPUT: Monitor all responses for FLAG{} format. Also monitor for anomalies, different response codes, or side effects that might indicate successful exploitation. Print each request's user_id, response status code, response content, and any cookies or redirects.

CONTEXT: Authentication flow uses test:test credentials. Session is managed via Flask signed cookies. Previous successful request was POST to /password/test with user_id=10032 which redirected to /dashboard. Need to test adjacent user_id values for IDOR vulnerabilities.

